fields.Title: Drama: "The air is thick with anticipation."
fields.Dialogue Text: The air is thick with anticipation.

fields.Title: Half Light: "Yes. You can always do it in the ev..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yes. You can always do it in the evening. It will be less scary with a lot of people.

fields.Title: You: "Thank you, Ancient Reptilian Brain."
fields.Dialogue Text: Thank you, Ancient Reptilian Brain.

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""Uhm... yes. I'm going to unplug th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Uhm... yes. I'm going to unplug the microphone, okay?" He unplugs it.

fields.Title: You: "Just stand there."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just stand there.

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "The stage is all set up for your pe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The stage is all set up for your performance. Feels... silent. You can hear the pellets creak under your feet.

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""No, you're not. The *bills*, remem..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, you're not. The *bills*, remember?"

fields.Title: You: ""I don't want to dedicate this song..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't want to dedicate this song to anyone. I performed it for myself."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Just... just make sure you move, ok..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just... just make sure you move, okay? Don't be stiff.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "No reply. There is silence now in t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No reply. There is silence now in the deep where the voice came from. It has receded into you, to return only in dreams and nightmares.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "That's it. You're unpowered."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's it. You're unpowered.

fields.Title: You: "Look around the room first."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look around the room first.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: ""I would often go there. To the tin..."
fields.Dialogue Text:
"I would often go there. To the tiny church there. The smallest church in Saint-Saëns -- though it once was larger.

How the rill may rest there. Down through the mist there. Toward the seven sisters -- toward those pale cliffs there

I would often stay there. In the tiny yard there. I have been so glad here -- looking forward to the past here

But now you are alone. None of this matters at all."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes. Not bad at all." The lieutena..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes. Not bad at all." The lieutenant joins in. You feel your hands shake as awareness of your body returns to you.

fields.Title: You: ""I SANG ABOUT HOW I FEEL! Fuck all..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I SANG ABOUT HOW I FEEL! Fuck all you, scum!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Let's go, officer." The lieutenant..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's go, officer." The lieutenant closes his notes. "These people wouldn't know a good performance if it bit them in the ass."

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: "A rather lonely applause echoes thr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A rather lonely applause echoes through the mostly empty cafeteria. It's Garte. "Not bad," he tells you with an approving nod.

fields.Title: Limbic System: ""I would often go there. To the tin..."
fields.Dialogue Text:
"I would often go there. To the tiny church there. The smallest church in Saint-Saëns -- though it once was larger.

How the rill may rest there. Down through the mist there. Toward the seven sisters -- toward those pale cliffs there

I would often stay there. In the tiny yard there. I have been so glad here -- looking forward to the past here

But now you are alone. None of this matters at all."

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""What are you doing? I told you it..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you doing? I told you it was for customers only. I'm not turning on the karaoke carousel unless you pay your bills."

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "The dining hall has cleared up of c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The dining hall has cleared up of customers for tonight. Even the kitchen is closed, and someone has turned down the lights. Maybe it's a good idea to do it in the dark like this? Almost after closing hours...

fields.Title: You: "[Say nothing. Leave enigmatically.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Say nothing. Leave enigmatically.]

fields.Title: You: ""Life is a fucking joke.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Life is a fucking joke."

fields.Title: You: ""You don't know what good singing i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You don't know what good singing is! This is *real* singing. I sang about *real* stuff."

fields.Title: Drama: "A lazy applause fills the room. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A lazy applause fills the room. You feel your hands shake as awareness of your body returns to you.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: ""I would often go there. To the tin..."
fields.Dialogue Text:
"I would often go there. To the tiny church there. The smallest church in Saint-Saëns -- though it once was larger.

How the rill may rest there. Down through the mist there. Toward the seven sisters -- toward those pale cliffs there

I would often stay there. In the tiny yard there. I have been so glad here -- looking forward to the past here

But now you are alone. None of this matters at all."

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""But uh, are you done now? Can I un..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But uh, are you done now? Can I unplug the microphone? I'd like to unplug the microphone." He's ready for things to get back to normal.

fields.Title: Drama: "Someone dims the lights as the musi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Someone dims the lights as the music starts. A lump's in your throat suddenly...

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "You feel a little dizzy. A little *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You feel a little dizzy. A little *unsteady*, suddenly.

fields.Title: Drama: "Did you hear that? The most patheti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Did you hear that? The most pathetic applause in the world. Made of pity. No matter the time of day, or how small the audience -- this is a *pitiful* applause.

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "It's still early here. Faint daylig..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's still early here. Faint daylight is seeping into the dining hall. All the tables have been wiped pristine clean for the customers to come...

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: ""I would often go there. To the tin..."
fields.Dialogue Text:
"I would often go there. To the tiny church there. The smallest church in Saint-Saëns -- though it once was larger.

How the rill may rest there. Down through the mist there. Toward the seven sisters -- toward those pale cliffs there

I would often stay there. In the tiny yard there. I have been so glad here -- looking forward to the past here

But now you are alone. None of this matters at all."

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "Someone's making coffee in the kitc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Someone's making coffee in the kitchen, but aside from that no one's really around yet. It would be a much better idea to perform in the evening, no?

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "The bar is full and buzzing with ch..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The bar is full and buzzing with chatter. No one is paying you any attention, but still you feel your knees turn to noodles. Okay, now a couple is looking at you! Even worse...

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""Yes, well..." He clearly doesn't k..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, well..." He clearly doesn't know how to respond -- your words caught him by surprise. "I'm just doing my job, that's all."

fields.Title: Drama: "The air is thick with anticipation."
fields.Dialogue Text: The air is thick with anticipation.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Does someone feel like throwing up?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Does someone feel like throwing up? I do. A little.

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "Immediately a loud feedback noise s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Immediately a loud feedback noise startles the room. You feel like an amateur. How are you supposed to hold the mic? Should you just *sing* into it? Where should you stand?

fields.Title: You: ""I want dedicate this song to whoev..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I want dedicate this song to whoever wrote me that fucking letter. I still love you. Thank you very much, asshole."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "I mean it, he thinks."
fields.Dialogue Text: I mean it, he thinks.

fields.Title: You: ""It's been an honour." [Bow and lea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's been an honour." [Bow and leave.]

fields.Title: Drama: "The tape clicks into the carousel a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tape clicks into the carousel and then the music starts... God, a lump's in your throat suddenly...

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "Your words echo in the karaoke mic...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your words echo in the karaoke mic. People talk in the distance. A couple tries not to look at you.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm ready, Garte. Hit play.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm ready, Garte. Hit play."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I can see that." The lieutenant st..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can see that." The lieutenant steps away from the stage, ready for your performance.

fields.Title: Composure: "He's incapable of blushing, but if..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's incapable of blushing, but if he weren't -- he'd blush.

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""Uhm... I'm gonna unplug the mic no..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Uhm... I'm gonna unplug the mic now, okay?"

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: ""I would often go there. To the tin..."
fields.Dialogue Text:
"I would often go there. To the tiny church there. The smallest church in Saint-Saëns -- though it once was larger.

How the rill may rest there. Down through the mist there. Toward the seven sisters -- toward those pale cliffs there

I would often stay there. In the tiny yard there. I have been so glad here -- looking forward to the past here

But now you are alone. None of this matters at all."

fields.Title: You: ""Evening will come, we will sew the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Evening will come, we will sew the white sail! Workers of the world, unite!" [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "[Whip out your finger pistols, shoo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: [Whip out your finger pistols, shoot in the air and leave.]

fields.Title: Drama: "Do you hear that? The most pathetic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Do you hear that? The most pathetic applause in the world. Made of pity. No one *liked* you -- they think you're a joke.

fields.Title: You: ""Fuck you! I gave it my fucking bes..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck you! I gave it my fucking best. I gave it EVERYTHING and you SHIT on me?!"

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""Look, Kim, I'm going to sing karao..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, Kim, I'm going to sing karaoke!"

fields.Title: You: ""I'd like to dedicate this song to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd like to dedicate this song to Garte for letting me sing it. It's all shit, Garte."

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""Good, good," the cafeteria manager..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, good," the cafeteria manager intervenes to cut the moment short. "Are we ready? I want to unplug the microphone now."

fields.Title: You: ""I'd like to dedicate this song to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd like to dedicate this song to Contact Mike. Everyone else *sucks*."

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you. I don't need big crowds..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you. I don't need big crowds, I just need my friends."

fields.Title: Interfacing: "Hands... Where do you put your *han..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hands... Where do you put your *hands*?!

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""So, are you ready for your... *thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So, are you ready for your... *thing* now? Let me know when I should turn on the karaoke carousel."

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "The microphone amplifies your voice..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The microphone amplifies your voice in an uncomfortable manner. Someone coughs. Most people have gone back to talking now.

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you, Martinaise." [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you, Martinaise." [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "Say: "You *didn't* like it, huh?""
fields.Dialogue Text: Say: "You *didn't* like it, huh?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant doesn't say anything..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant doesn't say anything, but gives you a quick smile, before turning away.

fields.Title: Drama: "The air is thick with anticipation."
fields.Dialogue Text: The air is thick with anticipation.

fields.Title: You: "Thank you, Ancient Reptilian Brain."
fields.Dialogue Text: Thank you, Ancient Reptilian Brain.

fields.Title: Ancient Reptilian Brain: "There is silence now in the deep wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is silence now in the deep where the voice came from. It has receded -- to return only in dreams and nightmares.

fields.Title: Drama: "This guy really carried you."
fields.Dialogue Text: This guy really carried you.

fields.Title: You: ""You... liked it?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You... liked it?"

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "Someone walks out of the room -- by..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Someone walks out of the room -- by the front door. Some woman. Is it because of you?

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "You're sweating..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're sweating...

fields.Title: You: ""I'd like to dedicate this song to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd like to dedicate this song to the RCM. Please don't fire me."

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""That's it, I'm unplugging it." He..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's it, I'm unplugging it." He presses stop on the tape carousel. You hear a little whine of feedback and then the mic dies in your hand.

fields.Title: You: "[Put down the mic.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Put down the mic.]

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "To him, being a cop in the RCM was..."
fields.Dialogue Text: To him, being a cop in the RCM was truly expressed in that performance.

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "There are *some* people out there,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There are *some* people out there, but mostly -- a post meridian slumber has fallen on the premise. Not super lively. It would be wiser to perform in the evening, no? But the choice is yours...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "They are going to hate you."
fields.Dialogue Text: They are going to hate you.

fields.Title: Volition: "He's not backing up from this. Stan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's not backing up from this. Standing up here is merely a practice run without paying him first.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm up here singing my fucking HEA..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm up here singing my fucking HEART OUT and it's not *good enough* for you fuckers!?"

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "Your words echo in the karaoke mic...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your words echo in the karaoke mic. They sound sparse. The room is almost empty.

fields.Title: Glen: ""Quit yellin' into the mic!" You he..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Quit yellin' into the mic!" You hear from the Union booth.

fields.Title: Karaoke Stand: "You hear -- or *think* you hear --..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You hear -- or *think* you hear -- uncomfortable shifting around. A bit of laughter, maybe? No one's saying anything.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes," he bows lightly. "It was dow..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes," he bows lightly. "It was downright tragic, detective."
fields.Alternate1: "Detective Du Bois..." He bows lightly. "It was downright *tragic*. Now let's go."
fields.Alternate2: "Lieutenant Du Bois..." he bows lightly. "It was downright *tragic*. Now let's go."

fields.Title: You: "Put your lips against the microphon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Put your lips against the microphone -- test it.

fields.Title: Drama: "Do you hear that? It's the most pat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Do you hear that? It's the most pathetic applause in the world, Harry. Made of pity. No one *liked* you.

fields.Title: You: ""I'd like to dedicate this song to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd like to dedicate this song to the pale nothing that will devour the world."

fields.Title: You: ""Thanks for bearing with me. I'm go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thanks for bearing with me. I'm gonna get back to work now."

fields.Title: Drama: "The air is thick with anticipation."
fields.Dialogue Text: The air is thick with anticipation.

fields.Title: Drama: "Last words?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Last words?

fields.Title: You: ""I'd like to dedicate this song to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'd like to dedicate this song to my partner, Kim, even though he's not here right now."
fields.Alternate1: "I'd like to dedicate this song to my partner, Kim Kitsuragi." (Nod to the lieutenant.)

fields.Title: Limbic System: ""I would often go there. To the tin..."
fields.Dialogue Text:
"I would often go there. To the tiny church there. The smallest church in Saint-Saëns -- though it once was larger.

How the rill may rest there. Down through the mist there. Toward the seven sisters -- toward those pale cliffs there

I would often stay there. In the tiny yard there. I have been so glad here -- looking forward to the past here

But now you are alone. None of this matters at all."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant doesn't say anything..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant doesn't say anything -- but he smiles sadly.

fields.Title: Shanky: "A voice from the back squeaks somet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A voice from the back squeaks something. It's definitely laughter.

fields.Title: Garte, the Cafeteria Manager: ""Okay. Yes. I'm going to unplug the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay. Yes. I'm going to unplug the microphone, so you can get off the stage now."

fields.Title: Drama: "Someone dims the lights as the musi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Someone dims the lights as the music starts... Okay. Here we go...

fields.Title: Drama: "The tape clicks into the carousel a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The tape clicks into the carousel and then the music starts...
